## The VS Split at 2ct: Where $70 Becomes $5,970

At 2ct, the VS grade premium transforms from a $70 footnote into a $5,970 decision. Both grades remain 100% eye-clean in round brilliants — the face-up result is identical. But the market prices the VS1 certificate at nearly $6,000 more because per-carat prices are higher at the 2ct weight tier and every clarity step costs more per carat.

This is The VS Split in its most consequential form. The $5,970 you spend to upgrade from VS2 to VS1 at 2ct purchases a different four-letter code on the GIA certificate. The diamond in the ring looks the same.

| Grade | Stone | Price | Per-Carat | Farzana's Analytical Verdict |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| [2ct G-VS2 GIA Excellent](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29307739?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) | 29307739 | $16,490 | $8,245/ct | 10/10. The 2ct Sweet Spot. This is the most efficient entry to a 2ct natural round diamond in G color. VS2 is 100% eye-clean at this weight. The $5,970 you keep over VS1 belongs in a better setting or a larger stone entirely. |
| [2ct G-VS2 GIA Excellent](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/27188428?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) | 27188428 | $18,540 | $9,270/ct | 8/10. The Premium VS2. $2,050 above the VS2 floor for superior light performance. At this price it overlaps VS1 territory — verify table %, depth %, and pavilion angle before choosing over the floor stone. |
| [2ct G-VS1 GIA Excellent](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29249620?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) | 29249620 | $22,460 | $11,230/ct | 7/10. The VS Split Entry. The cheapest VS1 at 2ct G. $5,970 more than the VS2 floor for a distinction invisible in wear. Buy this only if VS1 is a deliberate, informed choice — not a default assumption from a jeweler who benefits from upselling clarity. |
| [2ct G-VS1 GIA Excellent](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28531209?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) | 28531209 | $22,580 | $11,290/ct | 7/10. The VS1 Median. $120 above the VS1 floor. The price difference between the two VS1 entries is fluorescence or proportion specification — verify carefully before paying the additional premium over the $22,460 floor. |

**Data insight:** The VS premium at 2ct ($5,970) is 85 times the VS premium at 1ct ($70). The premium grows because 2ct per-carat prices are 2.55× higher than 1ct per-carat prices — every grade step is priced at 2ct rates, not 1ct rates. The face-up visual result at both weights is identical.

